What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Maritime Safety Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Maritime Safety Market

Rising trade and freight transport activities by sea has led to the rise in demand for maritime safety. Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the maritime safety market will exhibit a CAGR of 7.5% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. This signifies that the market value will rise up to USD 39.79 billion by the year 2028.

Maritime safety is a general and broad term that includes everything from the safety of workers to ship construction and maintenance. It is a term that defines undertaking safety measures of vessels both internally and externally. Apart from this, under maritime safety the coast guards are responsible for licensing mariners, documenting flag vessels, and much more. Maritime safety is referred to as a mission of the U.S. coast guard and is important because it protects an essential element of the U.S. economy.

Increased awareness and the need to maintain marine security have prompted the growth of the maritime safety market. The rapid rise in international trade via waterways has also led to the rise in demand for maritime safety. Rising demand for advanced security and safety mechanisms against terrorism has created lucrative growth opportunities for the maritime safety market. Supportive administrating rules and regulations have further induced market growth.

However, untapped and ungoverned marine zones will pose a challenge to the market growth rate. Economic downturns coupled with a lack of uniform standards for maritime safety technological solutions will also dampen the market growth rate.

